obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4816  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Immunoelectron microscopy detection of otoferlin (OTOF) in the mature auditory inner hair cell (IHC) ribbon synapse. The greatest density of 10 nm gold particles is associated with vesicles tethered to the active zone membrane.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Electron Microscopy. Mouse cochleas were fixed as described\"\n\nantibody:\n\nAuthors used 3 different antibodies against OTOF throughout this study, the N14 antibody was used for EM.\n\nFrom supplemental M&M: \"Two rabbit polyclonal antibodies and one mouse monoclonal antibody were generated against mouse otoferlin. The N14 immune serum was raised against the synthetic peptide GKTRSHKEEPQRQDEP (aa 196-211) located in the C2A-C2B interdomain, and the corresponding antibodies were affinity-purified.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4816" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
